CLEAN ENERGY FUTURE - LORDSTOWN, LLC REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE
Clean Energy Future - Lordstown, LLC ("CEF") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from an electric generation facility located in Lordstown, Ohio ("Facility") that is interconnected to the transmission system operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth CEF's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the Facility pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Service.
Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The total annual revenue requirement is $2,236,000.00.
The total monthly revenue requirement is $2,236,000.00 / 12 = $186,333.33.
The annual revenue requirement is divided among the three units that comprise the Facility as follows:
ST10 (336 MW) - $859,606.40
CT11 (269 MW) - $688,196.80
CT12 (269 MW) - $688,196.80
